content: That's really helpful to know. I'll have to plan my trips accordingly. I've been trying to get out at least once a week, and I've been keeping track of my sightings in my birding journal. It's been really rewarding to see the different species I've spotted so far. Speaking of which, I've seen 32 species so far this year, and I'm hoping to reach 50 by the end of summer. Do you think that's a realistic goal?
